# Development experience

Backoffice requires backend APIs running behind the dev proxy.

## Start stack

```bash
# Passport (8080)
cd ../passport && ./mvnw quarkus:dev

# Visita — domains UI (8081)
cd ../visita && ./mvnw quarkus:dev

# Backoffice (4200)
npm install
ng serve --proxy-config src/proxy.conf.json
```

Open [http://localhost:4200](http://localhost:4200).

## Dev login

- **User:** `cto-boss` (email `cto@passport.vepo.dev`) or use email on login form
- **Password:** `qwas1234` (Passport dev seed)

`cto-boss` has `passport.admin` and `domains.admin` via seeded profiles.

## When adding a feature

Before marking done, click through the new UI with the right role:

| Feature area | Login as |
|--------------|----------|
| Users / profiles / roles | `passport.admin` (e.g. cto-boss) |
| Domains | `domains.admin` (cto-boss has both) |
| No elevated menu | `junior` |

## Never

- Ship a screen that only works with manual API calls (no navigation path).
- Document features without verifying proxy + backend are up.
